# @carneirofc/ui is published to GitHub Packages, which requires auth even for
# public packages. Provide a GitHub Personal Access Token (classic) with the
# `read:packages` scope via NODE_AUTH_TOKEN before `npm install`:
#
#   Linux/macOS : export NODE_AUTH_TOKEN=ghp_xxx
#   PowerShell  : $env:NODE_AUTH_TOKEN = "ghp_xxx"
#
# The gh CLI token does NOT carry read:packages — create the PAT at
# github.com -> Settings -> Developer settings -> Personal access tokens.
@carneirofc:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${NODE_AUTH_TOKEN}
